<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER SERIES - INSTALL - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place mainshaft sliding clutches in neutral (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025j4">Figure 194</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the shift bars in the neutral position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025j5">inset, Figure 195</hotlnk>), install the shifter housing on the case, fitting
                the shift yokes into the slots of the sliding clutches.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025j4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025j4" filename="../figg13/G13025J4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 194. Place Mainshaft Sliding Clutches in Neutral</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f13025j5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025j5" filename="../figg13/G13025J5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 195. With Shift Bars in Neutral Position, Install Shifter Housing on Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13025j6">Figure 196</hotlnk>). Use the two longer bolts at the lifting eye locations.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13025j6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13025j6" filename="../figg13/G13025J6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 196. Install Retaining Bolts and Tighten</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
